text: 10/ Finally, double humanitarian aid. Still huge need to relieve suffering in and around Syria. Increase in refugee support to Jordan/Lebanon/Iraq ensures conflict is contained.
9/ Better leverage is a prospective Marshall Plan for Syria ‚Äì spend billions on reconstruction rather than on a military escalation that‚Äôs doomed to fail & kill lots of Americans.
8/ And time to realize our leverage in diplomacy is not our military presence in Syria. Hasn‚Äôt worked so far bc all sides know we have less at stake militarily than other parties.
7/ U.S. must end our absence from peace talks ‚Äì stop outsourcing diplomacy to Turkey and Russia.

6/ This doesn‚Äôt mean disengagement. Tillerson should change his schedule and go to Israel on Middle East trip. Make clear we will support Israel‚Äôs ability to defend its borders, increase funding for Israel‚Äôs protection.

5/ The continued military conflict in Syria is inevitable and it will be years until it ends. But it will last twice as long if U.S. gets more directly involved in the combat. Our presence will raise stakes for others.
4/ U.S. failure to understand local political and tribal dynamics dooms any military mission ‚Äì just like Iraq (and Syria is much more complicated than Iraq)

3/ Now, presence of thousands of U.S. troops is dragging us more directly into the many conflicts playing out in Syria:

SDF v. ISIS
Israel v. Iran
rebels v. Asad/Iran/Russia
Turkey v. Kurds

2/ U.S. military half measures over past 4 years have badly exacerbated the war. Building up Kurds to fight ISIS drew in Turkey, weak support for Syrian rebels gave them enough to continue, not enough to win.
